<exercise checkit-seed="0007" checkit-slug="TI6" checkit-title="Partial fractions">
    <statement>
        
        <p>
            Consider the partial fraction decomposition <me> \frac{5 \, {\left(x^{2} + x + 12\right)}}{x^{3} + 3 \, x^{2} + 9 \, x + 27}=\frac{5}{x^{2} + 9} + \frac{5}{x + 3}.</me>  Use this decomposition to compute <m>\displaystyle\int \frac{5 \, {\left(x^{2} + x + 12\right)}}{x^{3} + 3 \, x^{2} + 9 \, x + 27}dx</m>.
        </p>
    </statement>
    <answer>
        <me>\displaystyle\int \frac{5 \, {\left(x^{2} + x + 12\right)}}{x^{3} + 3 \, x^{2} + 9 \, x + 27}dx=\displaystyle\int \frac{5}{x^{2} + 9} + \frac{5}{x + 3}dx=\frac{5}{3} \, \arctan\left(\frac{1}{3} \, x\right) + 5 \, \log\left(x + 3\right)+C.</me>
    </answer>
</exercise>
